Context:
For rapid-fire notifications, send 5 calls concurrently with Promise.all:
```typescript
test('sends multiple notifications with unique IDs', async ({ mcpServer, extensionContext: _ext, mcpClient }) => {
  await waitForExtensionConnected(mcpServer);
  const results = await Promise.all(
    Array.from({ length: 5 }, (_, i) =>
      mcpClient.callTool('browser_notify', {
        title: `Notification ${i}`,
        message: `Message ${i}`,
      }),
    ),
  );
  const ids = results.map(r => {
    expect(r.isError).toBe(false);
    return parseToolResult(r.content).notificationId as string;
  });
  // All IDs are unique
  expect(new Set(ids).size).toBe(5);
});
```

For validation errors — the MCP server validates Zod schemas before dispatch. Missing required fields should result in `isError: true` responses. Pattern:
```typescript
test('returns error when title is missing', async ({ mcpServer, extensionContext: _ext, mcpClient }) => {
  await waitForExtensionConnected(mcpServer);
  const result = await mcpClient.callTool('browser_notify', { message: 'no title' });
  expect(result.isError).toBe(true);
});
```

For long strings, generate a 500-char title:
```typescript
const longTitle = 'A'.repeat(500);
const result = await mcpClient.callTool('browser_notify', { title: longTitle, message: 'test' });
expect(result.isError).toBe(false);
```

Constraints:
- All tests in the same file (e2e/browser-notify.e2e.ts)
- Each test.describe block should have a descriptive name
- Use parseToolResult from helpers.ts for all response parsing
